Note: Advanced Spatial Reasoning System for AI Agents
Note: Implements spatial logic, geometric reasoning, topological relations,
Note: spatial planning, qualitative spatial reasoning, and spatial knowledge representation

Note: Core spatial types
Type called "SpatialObject":
    object id as String
    object type as String  Note: "point", "line", "polygon", "region", "solid"
    coordinates as List[Float]  Note: Coordinate values
    coordinate system as String  Note: "cartesian", "polar", "geographic", "relative"
    dimensions as Integer  Note: 2D, 3D, etc.
    bounding box as List[Float]  Note: Min/max bounds
    properties as Dictionary  Note: Size, shape, orientation, etc.
    metadata as Dictionary

Type called "SpatialRelation":
    relation id as String
    relation type as String  Note: "topological", "directional", "distance", "orientation"
    subject as String  Note: Object ID
    object as String  Note: Object ID  
    relation name as String  Note: "contains", "north_of", "near", "parallel", etc.
    confidence as Float
    quantitative measure as Float  Note: Optional numeric measure
    context as Dictionary

Type called "SpatialRegion":
    region id as String
    region type as String  Note: "convex", "concave", "connected", "disconnected"
    boundary as List[SpatialObject]  Note: Objects forming the boundary
    interior points as List[SpatialObject]
    area as Float
    perimeter as Float
    centroid as List[Float]
    spatial properties as Dictionary

Type called "SpatialConstraint":
    constraint id as String
    constraint type as String  Note: "distance", "angle", "containment", "alignment"
    involved objects as List[String]
    constraint specification as Dictionary
    tolerance as Float
    priority as Float
    satisfaction method as String

Type called "QualitativeFrame":
    frame id as String
    frame type as String  Note: "RCC8", "9-intersection", "cardinal_directions", "relative_position"
    relations as List[String]  Note: Possible relations in this frame
    composition_table as Dictionary  Note: Relation composition rules
    inverse_table as Dictionary  Note: Relation inverses
    constraints as List[Dictionary]  Note: Frame-specific constraints

Type called "SpatialConfiguration":
    configuration id as String
    objects as List[SpatialObject]
    relations as List[SpatialRelation]
    constraints as List[SpatialConstraint]
    reference frame as QualitativeFrame
    global properties as Dictionary
    consistency status as String

Type called "SpatialPath":
    path id as String
    start location as SpatialObject
    end location as SpatialObject
    waypoints as List[SpatialObject]
    path type as String  Note: "euclidean", "manhattan", "geodesic", "constrained"
    total distance as Float
    constraints as List[SpatialConstraint]
    traversal cost as Float

Note: Topological reasoning (RCC-8)
Process called "compute_rcc8_relations" that takes object1 as SpatialObject and object2 as SpatialObject returns List[String]:
    Let possible_relations be empty list
    Let obj1_boundary be extract_boundary with object1
    Let obj1_interior be extract_interior with object1
    Let obj2_boundary be extract_boundary with object2
    Let obj2_interior be extract_interior with object2
    
    Note: Check 9-intersection model components
    Let interior_interior be intersect with obj1_interior and obj2_interior
    Let interior_boundary be intersect with obj1_interior and obj2_boundary
    Let interior_exterior be intersect with obj1_interior and complement of (union obj2_interior and obj2_boundary)
    Let boundary_interior be intersect with obj1_boundary and obj2_interior
    Let boundary_boundary be intersect with obj1_boundary and obj2_boundary
    Let boundary_exterior be intersect with obj1_boundary and complement of (union obj2_interior and obj2_boundary)
    Let exterior_interior be intersect with complement of (union obj1_interior and obj1_boundary) and obj2_interior
    Let exterior_boundary be intersect with complement of (union obj1_interior and obj1_boundary) and obj2_boundary
    
    Note: Determine RCC-8 relation based on 9-intersection pattern
    If is_empty with interior_interior and is_empty with interior_boundary and is_empty with boundary_interior and is_empty with boundary_boundary:
        Add "DC" to possible_relations  Note: Disconnected
    
    If is_non_empty with boundary_boundary and is_empty with interior_interior and is_empty with interior_boundary and is_empty with boundary_interior:
        Add "EC" to possible_relations  Note: Externally Connected
    
    If is_non_empty with interior_interior and is_non_empty with interior_boundary and is_non_empty with boundary_interior and is_non_empty with boundary_boundary:
        Note: Check for partial overlap
        If is_non_empty with interior_exterior and is_non_empty with exterior_interior:
            Add "PO" to possible_relations  Note: Partial Overlap
    
    If is_non_empty with interior_interior and is_empty with interior_boundary and is_non_empty with boundary_interior and is_non_empty with boundary_boundary and is_empty with exterior_interior:
        Add "TPP" to possible_relations  Note: Tangential Proper Part
    
    If is_non_empty with interior_interior and is_non_empty with interior_boundary and is_empty with boundary_interior and is_non_empty with boundary_boundary and is_empty with exterior_interior:
        Add "TPPi" to possible_relations  Note: Tangential Proper Part Inverse
    
    If is_non_empty with interior_interior and is_empty with interior_boundary and is_empty with boundary_interior and is_empty with boundary_boundary and is_empty with exterior_interior:
        Add "NTPP" to possible_relations  Note: Non-Tangential Proper Part
    
    If is_non_empty with interior_interior and is_empty with interior_boundary and is_empty with boundary_interior and is_empty with boundary_boundary and is_empty with exterior_interior:
        Add "NTPPi" to possible_relations  Note: Non-Tangential Proper Part Inverse
    
    If is_non_empty with interior_interior and is_empty with interior_boundary and is_empty with boundary_interior and is_non_empty with boundary_boundary and is_empty with exterior_interior and is_empty with interior_exterior:
        Add "EQ" to possible_relations  Note: Equal
    
    Return possible_relations

Process called "apply_rcc8_composition" that takes relation1 as String and relation2 as String returns List[String]:
    Note: RCC-8 composition table - returns possible relations from composition
    Let composition_table be create_rcc8_composition_table
    Let composition_key be relation1 Joined with "_" Joined with relation2
    
    If composition_table contains key composition_key:
        Return composition_table with key composition_key
    Otherwise:
        Return empty list

Process called "check_rcc8_consistency" that takes relations as List[SpatialRelation] returns Dictionary:
    Let objects be extract_unique_objects with relations
    Let constraint_network be build_rcc8_constraint_network with relations and objects
    Let consistency_result be solve_rcc8_constraints with constraint_network
    
    Return dictionary with keys "consistent", "violated_constraints", "minimal_conflict":
        "consistent" maps to consistency_result with field satisfiable
        "violated_constraints" maps to consistency_result with field violations
        "minimal_conflict" maps to find_minimal_conflict with consistency_result

Note: Directional and distance reasoning
Process called "compute_directional_relations" that takes objects as List[SpatialObject] and reference_frame as String returns List[SpatialRelation]:
    Let directional_relations be empty list
    
    For i from 0 to length of objects minus 1:
        For j from i plus 1 to length of objects minus 1:
            Let obj1 be objects with index i
            Let obj2 be objects with index j
            
            Let direction be compute_direction with obj1 and obj2 and reference_frame
            Let distance be compute_distance with obj1 and obj2
            
            If direction is not equal to null:
                Let relation be create_spatial_relation_structure
                Set relation with field subject to obj1 with field object_id
                Set relation with field object to obj2 with field object_id
                Set relation with field relation_type to "directional"
                Set relation with field relation_name to direction
                Set relation with field quantitative_measure to distance
                Set relation with field confidence to 1.0
                
                Add relation to directional_relations
    
    Return directional_relations

Process called "compute_direction" that takes obj1 as SpatialObject and obj2 as SpatialObject and reference_frame as String returns String:
    Let coords1 be obj1 with field coordinates
    Let coords2 be obj2 with field coordinates
    
    If reference_frame is equal to "cardinal":
        Let dx be coords2 with index 0 minus coords1 with index 0
        Let dy be coords2 with index 1 minus coords1 with index 1
        
        Note: Determine cardinal direction
        If absolute_value of dx is greater than absolute_value of dy:
            If dx is greater than 0:
                Return "east"
            Otherwise:
                Return "west"
        Otherwise:
            If dy is greater than 0:
                Return "north"
            Otherwise:
                Return "south"
    
    If reference_frame is equal to "relative":
        Note: Compute relative direction based on object orientation
        Let obj1_orientation be obj1 with field properties with key "orientation" or 0.0
        Let angle_to_obj2 be compute_angle with coords1 and coords2
        Let relative_angle be angle_to_obj2 minus obj1_orientation
        
        Note: Normalize angle to [0, 2π)
        While relative_angle is less than 0:
            Set relative_angle to relative_angle plus 6.283185307  Note: 2π
        While relative_angle is greater than or equal to 6.283185307:
            Set relative_angle to relative_angle minus 6.283185307
        
        Note: Map angle to relative direction
        If relative_angle is less than 0.785398163:  Note: π/4
            Return "front"
        If relative_angle is less than 2.356194490:  Note: 3π/4
            Return "right"
        If relative_angle is less than 3.926990817:  Note: 5π/4
            Return "back"
        If relative_angle is less than 5.497787144:  Note: 7π/4
            Return "left"
        Otherwise:
            Return "front"
    
    Return null

Process called "compute_distance" that takes obj1 as SpatialObject and obj2 as SpatialObject returns Float:
    Let coords1 be obj1 with field coordinates
    Let coords2 be obj2 with field coordinates
    Let coordinate_system be obj1 with field coordinate_system
    
    If coordinate_system is equal to "cartesian":
        Return compute_euclidean_distance with coords1 and coords2
    
    If coordinate_system is equal to "geographic":
        Return compute_haversine_distance with coords1 and coords2
    
    If coordinate_system is equal to "manhattan":
        Return compute_manhattan_distance with coords1 and coords2
    
    Return compute_euclidean_distance with coords1 and coords2  Note: Default

Process called "compute_euclidean_distance" that takes coords1 as List[Float] and coords2 as List[Float] returns Float:
    Let sum_of_squares be 0.0
    Let dimensions be minimum of (length of coords1) and (length of coords2)
    
    For i from 0 to dimensions minus 1:
        Let diff be coords1 with index i minus coords2 with index i
        Set sum_of_squares to sum_of_squares plus (diff times diff)
    
    Return square_root of sum_of_squares

Note: Spatial path planning
Process called "plan_spatial_path" that takes start as SpatialObject and goal as SpatialObject and obstacles as List[SpatialObject] and constraints as List[SpatialConstraint] returns SpatialPath:
    Let path_planner be create_path_planner with constraints
    Let path_result be search_for_path with path_planner and start and goal and obstacles
    
    If path_result with field found is equal to true:
        Let optimized_path be optimize_path with path_result with field path and constraints
        Let path_cost be calculate_path_cost with optimized_path
        
        Let spatial_path be create_spatial_path_structure
        Set spatial_path with field start_location to start
        Set spatial_path with field end_location to goal
        Set spatial_path with field waypoints to optimized_path with field waypoints
        Set spatial_path with field total_distance to optimized_path with field total_distance
        Set spatial_path with field traversal_cost to path_cost
        Set spatial_path with field constraints to constraints
        
        Return spatial_path
    Otherwise:
        Return null

Process called "search_for_path" that takes planner as Dictionary and start as SpatialObject and goal as SpatialObject and obstacles as List[SpatialObject] returns Dictionary:
    Let algorithm be planner with key "algorithm"
    
    If algorithm is equal to "a_star":
        Return a_star_search with start and goal and obstacles and planner
    
    If algorithm is equal to "rrt":
        Return rrt_search with start and goal and obstacles and planner
    
    If algorithm is equal to "dijkstra":
        Return dijkstra_search with start and goal and obstacles and planner
    
    If algorithm is equal to "visibility_graph":
        Return visibility_graph_search with start and goal and obstacles and planner
    
    Return a_star_search with start and goal and obstacles and planner  Note: Default

Process called "a_star_search" that takes start as SpatialObject and goal as SpatialObject and obstacles as List[SpatialObject] and planner as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let open_set be priority queue containing start
    Let came_from be empty dictionary
    Let g_score be dictionary with key (start with field object_id) mapped to 0.0
    Let f_score be dictionary with key (start with field object_id) mapped to compute_heuristic with start and goal
    
    While open_set is not empty:
        Let current be remove minimum from open_set based on f_score
        
        If current equals goal:
            Let path be reconstruct_path with came_from and current
            Return dictionary with keys "found", "path", "cost":
                "found" maps to true
                "path" maps to path
                "cost" maps to g_score with key (current with field object_id)
        
        Let neighbors be find_valid_neighbors with current and obstacles and planner
        For each neighbor in neighbors:
            Let tentative_g_score be g_score with key (current with field object_id) plus compute_distance with current and neighbor
            
            If g_score does not contain key (neighbor with field object_id) or tentative_g_score is less than g_score with key (neighbor with field object_id):
                Set came_from with key (neighbor with field object_id) to current
                Set g_score with key (neighbor with field object_id) to tentative_g_score
                Set f_score with key (neighbor with field object_id) to tentative_g_score plus compute_heuristic with neighbor and goal
                
                If open_set does not contain neighbor:
                    Add neighbor to open_set
    
    Return dictionary with keys "found", "path", "cost":
        "found" maps to false
        "path" maps to null
        "cost" maps to infinity

Note: Qualitative spatial reasoning
Process called "perform_qualitative_reasoning" that takes configuration as SpatialConfiguration and query as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let frame_type be configuration with field reference_frame with field frame_type
    Let reasoning_result be empty dictionary
    
    If frame_type is equal to "RCC8":
        Set reasoning_result to reason_with_rcc8 with configuration and query
    
    If frame_type is equal to "cardinal_directions":
        Set reasoning_result to reason_with_cardinal_directions with configuration and query
    
    If frame_type is equal to "relative_position":
        Set reasoning_result to reason_with_relative_positions with configuration and query
    
    If frame_type is equal to "9_intersection":
        Set reasoning_result to reason_with_9_intersection with configuration and query
    
    Note: Apply spatial constraints
    Let constraint_satisfaction be check_spatial_constraints with configuration with field constraints and reasoning_result
    Set reasoning_result with key "constraint_satisfaction" to constraint_satisfaction
    
    Return reasoning_result

Process called "reason_with_cardinal_directions" that takes configuration as SpatialConfiguration and query as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let objects be configuration with field objects
    Let relations be configuration with field relations
    Let query_type be query with key "type"
    
    If query_type is equal to "compute_relations":
        Let computed_relations be compute_directional_relations with objects and "cardinal"
        Return dictionary with keys "computed_relations", "consistency":
            "computed_relations" maps to computed_relations
            "consistency" maps to check_cardinal_consistency with computed_relations
    
    If query_type is equal to "spatial_inference":
        Let target_object be query with key "target_object"
        Let reference_object be query with key "reference_object"
        Let inferred_direction be infer_cardinal_direction with target_object and reference_object and relations
        Return dictionary with keys "inferred_direction", "confidence":
            "inferred_direction" maps to inferred_direction with field direction
            "confidence" maps to inferred_direction with field confidence
    
    Return empty dictionary

Note: Spatial constraint satisfaction
Process called "solve_spatial_constraints" that takes constraints as List[SpatialConstraint] and objects as List[SpatialObject] returns Dictionary:
    Let constraint_network be build_spatial_constraint_network with constraints and objects
    Let solution_method be determine_solution_method with constraint_network
    
    If solution_method is equal to "geometric_algebra":
        Return solve_with_geometric_algebra with constraint_network
    
    If solution_method is equal to "constraint_propagation":
        Return solve_with_constraint_propagation with constraint_network
    
    If solution_method is equal to "optimization":
        Return solve_with_optimization with constraint_network
    
    Return solve_with_constraint_propagation with constraint_network  Note: Default

Process called "build_spatial_constraint_network" that takes constraints as List[SpatialConstraint] and objects as List[SpatialObject] returns Dictionary:
    Let network be empty dictionary
    Let variables be empty list
    Let domains be empty dictionary
    Let constraint_graph be empty dictionary
    
    Note: Create variables for object positions and properties
    For each object in objects:
        Let position_var be object with field object_id Joined with "_position"
        Let orientation_var be object with field object_id Joined with "_orientation"
        Add position_var to variables
        Add orientation_var to variables
        
        Note: Define domains based on object constraints
        Set domains with key position_var to create_position_domain with object
        Set domains with key orientation_var to create_orientation_domain with object
    
    Note: Add spatial constraints
    For each constraint in constraints:
        Let constraint_type be constraint with field constraint_type
        Let involved_objects be constraint with field involved_objects
        
        If constraint_type is equal to "distance":
            Add distance constraint to constraint_graph with involved_objects and constraint
        
        If constraint_type is equal to "angle":
            Add angle constraint to constraint_graph with involved_objects and constraint
        
        If constraint_type is equal to "containment":
            Add containment constraint to constraint_graph with involved_objects and constraint
        
        If constraint_type is equal to "alignment":
            Add alignment constraint to constraint_graph with involved_objects and constraint
    
    Set network with key "variables" to variables
    Set network with key "domains" to domains
    Set network with key "constraints" to constraint_graph
    
    Return network

Note: Mental spatial models and reasoning
Process called "construct_spatial_mental_model" that takes spatial_descriptions as List[String] and context as Dictionary returns SpatialConfiguration:
    Let parsed_descriptions be empty list
    
    Note: Parse natural language spatial descriptions
    For each description in spatial_descriptions:
        Let parsed be parse_spatial_description with description
        Add parsed to parsed_descriptions
    
    Note: Extract spatial objects and relations
    Let objects be extract_spatial_objects with parsed_descriptions
    Let relations be extract_spatial_relations with parsed_descriptions
    
    Note: Resolve ambiguities and inconsistencies
    Let resolved_objects be resolve_spatial_ambiguities with objects and context
    Let consistent_relations be ensure_spatial_consistency with relations and resolved_objects
    
    Note: Build spatial configuration
    Let configuration be create_spatial_configuration_structure
    Set configuration with field objects to resolved_objects
    Set configuration with field relations to consistent_relations
    Set configuration with field reference_frame to determine_reference_frame with parsed_descriptions
    
    Note: Validate and complete the model
    Let validation_result be validate_spatial_model with configuration
    If validation_result with field valid is equal to false:
        Set configuration to repair_spatial_model with configuration and validation_result
    
    Return configuration

Process called "parse_spatial_description" that takes description as String returns Dictionary:
    Let parsed_elements be empty dictionary
    Let spatial_keywords be list containing "north", "south", "east", "west", "above", "below", "left", "right", "inside", "outside", "near", "far", "between", "adjacent"
    
    Note: Extract spatial objects (nouns)
    Let objects be extract_nouns with description
    Set parsed_elements with key "objects" to objects
    
    Note: Extract spatial relations (prepositions and spatial keywords)
    Let relations be empty list
    For each keyword in spatial_keywords:
        If description contains keyword:
            Let relation_context be extract_relation_context with description and keyword
            Add relation_context to relations
    Set parsed_elements with key "relations" to relations
    
    Note: Extract quantitative information (distances, angles, sizes)
    Let quantities be extract_quantities with description
    Set parsed_elements with key "quantities" to quantities
    
    Note: Extract reference frames (coordinate systems, perspectives)
    Let reference_indicators be extract_reference_indicators with description
    Set parsed_elements with key "reference_frame" to reference_indicators
    
    Return parsed_elements

Note: Main spatial reasoning coordination
Process called "create_spatial_reasoner" that takes configuration as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let reasoner be empty dictionary
    
    Set reasoner with key "coordinate_system" to configuration with key "coordinate_system" or "cartesian"
    Set reasoner with key "qualitative_framework" to configuration with key "qualitative_framework" or "RCC8"
    Set reasoner with key "path_planning_algorithm" to configuration with key "path_planning" or "a_star"
    Set reasoner with key "constraint_solver" to configuration with key "constraint_solver" or "propagation"
    Set reasoner with key "uncertainty_handling" to configuration with key "uncertainty" or "fuzzy"
    Set reasoner with key "performance_metrics" to empty dictionary
    
    Return reasoner

Process called "execute_spatial_reasoning" that takes reasoner as Dictionary and query as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let query_type be query with key "type"
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    If query_type is equal to "topological_relations":
        Let objects be query with key "objects"
        Let relations be compute_all_topological_relations with objects
        Set result with key "relations" to relations
    
    If query_type is equal to "directional_relations":
        Let objects be query with key "objects"
        Let reference_frame be query with key "reference_frame" or "cardinal"
        Let directions be compute_directional_relations with objects and reference_frame
        Set result with key "directions" to directions
    
    If query_type is equal to "path_planning":
        Let start be query with key "start"
        Let goal be query with key "goal"
        Let obstacles be query with key "obstacles" or empty list
        Let constraints be query with key "constraints" or empty list
        Let path be plan_spatial_path with start and goal and obstacles and constraints
        Set result with key "path" to path
    
    If query_type is equal to "qualitative_reasoning":
        Let configuration be query with key "configuration"
        Let qualitative_query be query with key "qualitative_query"
        Let qualitative_result be perform_qualitative_reasoning with configuration and qualitative_query
        Set result to qualitative_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "constraint_satisfaction":
        Let constraints be query with key "constraints"
        Let objects be query with key "objects"
        Let solution be solve_spatial_constraints with constraints and objects
        Set result to solution
    
    If query_type is equal to "mental_model":
        Let descriptions be query with key "descriptions"
        Let context be query with key "context" or empty dictionary
        Let mental_model be construct_spatial_mental_model with descriptions and context
        Set result with key "mental_model" to mental_model
    
    Note: Add metadata
    Set result with key "reasoning_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    Set result with key "reasoner_config" to extract_reasoner_summary with reasoner
    
    Return result